          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2019-09-30 20:11:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Verified+1\n\nPassed enforced test review-ldiskfs-dne on CentOS 7.0/x86_64 uploaded by Onyx Autotest from onyx-38vm1: https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/aaad1d99-f9d8-4c7e-a052-4f012a02f887 ran 4 tests.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d056b39023b0c13b93e4e96ad02bdbdff688138b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-01 00:25:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAre you adding support to include the same interface (ib0) to two different nets (o2ib1, o2ib2) ? Amir, Olaf  is this a valid thing to do with DLC? I remember doing something similar with Gemini on Titan. In that case we created 16 virtual gni interfaces (gni0:0 -> gni0:16) and controlled traffic flow to individual OSS servers\nthis way. Is their a advantage with this approach?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "5f81f9c45469ba7fd39c65640bf762693c04c5f3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-01 01:33:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Are you adding support to include the same interface (ib0) to two\n > different nets (o2ib1, o2ib2) ? Amir, Olaf  is this a valid thing\n > to do with DLC? I remember doing something similar with Gemini on\n > Titan. In that case we created 16 virtual gni interfaces (gni0:0 ->\n > gni0:16) and controlled traffic flow to individual OSS servers\n > this way. Is their a advantage with this approach?\n\nI am _restoring_ this functionality. It is fundamental to fine grained routing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "425daa31f42ee0f1cb54aed2030f3cc13c12e423",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-01 13:40:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWe (ORNL) didn't know if this was a valid configuration. When we did fine grain routing we created \"virtual\" devices gni0:0 - gni0:16 and then attached each one to a net. Just asking Amir / Olaf if both approaches are allowed in the DLC API or was this setup something that just happened to work but was not allowed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "698f201571b6611ee7f917d0b8262ffea40fefd9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-01 13:44:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAlso has anyone tried this with socklnd? I don't see this kind of setup in the LND driver.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "38f282a5aa13ca071fd0a279715360f7f4b49ef4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-01 14:04:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nCan you add a test case to your sanity lnet test suite.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "aba790b4d0f89886c57b86a607709732b04858d7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-01 14:09:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nI'm like to see a test for this to show what configuration fails.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "584b816a586ac68f5e9fc5fd0378821c72058e1d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-01 14:18:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> I'm like to see a test for this to show what configuration fails.\n\nThat information is in the ticket.\n\nI can add a test-case, but this bug requires IB hardware, so it seems like a low value add.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "9994fb87fc1c3a02adecc2e120878b653df4166b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
